# CinemaRank
CinemaRank is an application that ranks movies from a dataset of over 100,000 films using a SplayTree and MaxHeap. Users can search based on vote count or rating, and compare the performance of both datastructures.

## Dataset
Download the TMDB dataset from Kaggle and place the CSV in a data/ folder inside the project directory.
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/asaniczka/tmdb-movies-dataset-2023-930k-movies

## Build & Run
g++ -std=c++17 -Wall -O2 main.cpp CSVReader.cpp -o cinemarank
./cinemarank

## Usage
Select option 1 to load the dataset, then use options 2-7 to query and compare results.